cs.SD, cs.CL, cs.SI, cs.AI, cs.LG

The paper discusses the principles of structure building in language, music, and animal song, which are all related to formal language theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SD (Sound), which deals with audio and music processing. The paper also discusses the complexities of language, which suggests a possible fit with cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper discusses the benefits and shortcomings of using the Chomsky hierarchy, which relates to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
